title: TMZ
summary: TMZ is a tabloid journalism online newspaper owned by Fox Corporation. It debuted on November 8, 2005. It was a collaboration between AOL and Telepictures, a division of Warner Bros.,[3] until Time Warner divested AOL in 2009. On September 13, 2021, WarnerMedia sold the site to Fox Corporation (itself a spinoff of divested news assets obtained from the acquisition of 21st Century Fox by the Walt Disney Company) as part of its parent company AT&Tâ€™s restructuring.[4][5]
